ğŸ” Spotting Testnet Scams and Protecting Your Funds

Scammers are tricking users by sending testnet TON instead of mainnet TON, making it seem like a legitimate payment. Once the victim sends crypto or an item in return, the scammer disappearsâ€”leaving them with worthless testnet funds.

How to Protect Yourself:

ğŸ”¹ Check if your wallet is on the mainnet. Testnet and mainnet are completely separate networksâ€”you cannot send funds between them.
ğŸ”¹ Verify your wallet address format. Mainnet addresses always start with UQ or EQ, while testnet addresses start with 0Q or KQ.
ğŸ”¹ Use trusted P2P platforms for exchanges and always double-check transactions.
ğŸ”¹ Be cautious. If a deal seems suspicious, donâ€™t proceed.
ğŸ”¹ Need help? Contact our support team at @tonkeeper.

ğŸ‘‰ Stay alert and always confirm youâ€™re on the mainnet before accepting payments!
